comments: Randle (NYK) establishes his right foot as his pivot and maintains it as he starts his dribble.
Vucevic (CHI) initiates contact with Randle's (NYK) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
DeRozan (CHI) goes to, not through, Randle's (NYK) space and marginal contact occurs as DeRozan releases away during the drive.
Randle (NYK) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with DeRozan's (CHI) arm after the release.
Williams (CHI) legally contests Randle's (NYK) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
DeRozan (CHI) initiates contact with Grimes' (NYK) arm which affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Randle (NYK) jumps alongside LaVine's (CHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
LaVine (CHI) moves alongside Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Vucevic (CHI) establishes himself in Grimes' (NYK) path and marginal lower body contact occurs during the pick.
Robinson (NYK) legally contests LaVine's (CHI) driving shot attempt.
Dosunmu (CHI) commits a take foul on Brunson (NYK).
Grimes (NYK) brings his hands toward LaVine (CHI) and marginal contact occurs as the pick is set.
LaVine (CHI) establishes himself in Barrett's (NYK) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Grimes (NYK) jumps A to B into DeRozan's (CHI) body and initiates contact that affects his jump shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it is deemed that DeRozan's (CHI) free throw makes contact with the rim and CHI is given possession with 0.3 seconds remaining.
